<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-17T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-17T22:00:00-05:00" n="447" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2739: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-18T11:00:00+08:00">November 18, 1931—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 18—5:15
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>955. By mandate of National Government issued yesterday General Wan
                            Fu-lin’s resignation as Chairman of Heilungkiang is accepted and General
                            Ma Chan-shan is appointed in his stead.</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>